headline: Aflac price target raised to $113 from $108 at Morgan Stanley
summary: Morgan Stanley analyst Bob Huang raised the firm’s price target on Aflac (AFL) to $113 from $108 and keeps an Equal Weight rating on the shares. Following Q2 results, the firm is updating its price targets for stocks in the Life Insurance segment under its coverage, the analyst tells investors. Nearly half of the life insurers under its coverage beat expectations on a reported basis and most exceeded expectations on a core basis, the firm adds.
